So 1 = 13 - 3 * (17 - 1 * 13) = 13 - 3 * 17 + 3 * 13 = 4 * 13 - 3 * 17
But 13 = 30 - 1 * 17
So 1 = 4 * (30 - 1 * 17) - 3 * 17 = 4 * 30 - 4 * 17 - 3 * 17 = 4 * 30 - 7 * 17
But 17 = 47 - 1 * 30
So 1 = 4 * 30 - 7 * (47 - 1 * 30) = 4 * 30 - 7 * 47 + 7 * 30 = 11 * 30 - 7 * 47

Therefore, $11 \cdot 30 \equiv 1 \pmod{47}$, so the inverse of 30 modulo 47 is 11.

Now we can multiply both sides of $30y \equiv 42 \pmod{47}$ by 11:
$11 \cdot 30y \equiv 11 \cdot 42 \pmod{47}$
